Document: BoxMesh
Path: godot/classes/class_boxmesh.rst
Summary: Creates an axis-aligned box primitive mesh with customizable UV layout and subdivision settings.

Generate an axis-aligned box PrimitiveMesh. The box's UV layout uses a 3×2 arrangement allowing individual face texturing. To apply uniform texturing across all faces, set the material's UV property to Vector3(3, 2, 1). This achieves the same result as adding "UV *= vec2(3.0, 2.0)" in a vertex shader.

Note: When using large textured BoxMesh (e.g. as a floor), UV jittering may occur depending on camera angle. Increase subdivide_depth, subdivide_height, and subdivide_width until UV jittering is eliminated.
---CHUNK---
